news_insight_text_link.news_insight_description: Ascend Elements is collaborating with Ernst & Young LLP on logistics for America's first EV battery materials manufacturing facility. It has also formed a joint venture, AE Elemental, with Elemental Strategic Metals for EV battery recycling in Poland and announced shipping sustainable cathode materials to Freudenberg. Additionally, a partnership with Call2Recycle aims to enhance EV battery management and recycling services.

org_similarity_summary.insight_similar_orgs: Ascend Elements, Farasis Energy, Blue Current, Octillion Power Systems, Flux Power, and Prieto Battery are all involved in the sustainable battery manufacturing sector. Farasis Energy, Blue Current, Octillion Power Systems, and Prieto Battery focus on developing and manufacturing lithium-ion batteries for various applications, while Flux Power specializes in supplying lithium battery packs for industrial and material handling equipment industries.

research_insight_text_link.research_insight_description: Ascend Elements is focused on advancing sustainable battery material recovery techniques. Their R&D efforts include methods for recycling lithium iron phosphate (LFP) batteries by adding oxidizing agents to form a leach solution, which is then filtered to reclaim materials. They are also developing processes for recycling all solid-state batteries (ASSBs) by neutralizing undesired reactions with passivating substances. Additionally, they have devised a method for recovering anode materials, specifically graphite, from a precipitate derived from cathode recycling streams. These innovations highlight Ascend Elements' commitment to enhancing the sustainability of battery materials.

overview_description.description: Ascend Elements manufactures advanced battery materials using valuable elements reclaimed from spent lithium-ion batteries. It uses hydroprocess recycling and direct recycling, which take old cathode material down to the atomic level to create new cathode materials. It also helps clients have the maximum return on assets to economically drive recycling and low-cost battery materials.

properties.growth_insight_description: Ascend Elements may be growing as evidenced by several key financial and operational indicators. The company has been named to Fast Company's Annual List of the World's Most Innovative Companies of 2024, which suggests recognition for its innovative approach in the industry. Additionally, Ascend Elements has secured a significant amount of funding, with reports indicating a $162 million investment for a recycled battery material plant. This influx of capital is a strong indicator of investor confidence and financial growth. Furthermore, the company is expanding its global footprint by forming a joint venture in Europe for EV battery recycling and starting operations in Poland, demonstrating an increase in its operational capabilities and market reach.

about_short_description.short_description: Ascend Elements manufactures sustainable battery materials using elements from discarded lithium-ion batteries.

product.name: Hydro-to-Cathode® Direct Precursor Synthesis
product.description: A patented process that transforms discarded lithium-ion batteries and manufacturing scrap into high-value cathode materials for EV batteries.

product.name: Cathode Active Materials (CAM)
product.description: Engineered materials made to precise specifications for use in lithium-ion batteries, produced from recycled battery elements.

product.name: Precursor Cathode Active Materials (pCAM)
product.description: Intermediate materials used in the production of cathode active materials, derived from recycled lithium-ion batteries.

product.name: Hydro-to-Anode® Graphite Purification
product.description: A process for recovering and purifying graphite from spent lithium-ion batteries for reuse in new batteries.

product.name: Full-Service EV Battery Recycling
product.description: Comprehensive recycling services for lithium-ion batteries, including logistics, materials tracking, and secure destruction of proprietary information.

product.name: Commodity Materials
product.description: Intermediate commodity metals sourced from recycled lithium-ion batteries for use in battery production or other applications.
